<article>
    <header><h1>Nikos Miras</h1></header>
      <p>Nick Miras has proved himself to be a very good studio and live performer in various occasions. Since 10 years old he started “practicing” on chairs and barrels. He has played with many bands since he was 15, such as Gothazar, Onyx, Celestial Ode and Verbal Delirium. Since 2003 he founded art of simplicity, along with Matthew Dakoutros. With Emmono Grizo he recorded the first two albums of the band and performed live all over Greece. He has also recorded several demos and official releases and has appeared in many recordings as guest musician.He has been a drum teacher in the National Conservatory (Sparta branch). He has also been an active member on several seminars. Nick has taken drum lessons for 7 years from various teachers. He has also studied some ethnic percussions, classical theory and piano.</p> 
